=== Etymology ===
From Middle English ''sille'' coming from Old English ''syll'' meaning "threshold".

== [[noun]] ==
#a horizontal [[slat]] which forms the [[base]] of a [[window]]. 
#:''She looked out the window resting her elbows on the window sill''.
